    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/matlab-package-execution/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here, we describe a method to address the problem of finding correspondence between datasets. As it only requires the features' retention time, m/z, and (optionally) feature intensity values (RT, MZ, FI) averaged across samples, it is simple to use and potentially applicable in the widest range of situations.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes the method as requiring RT and m/z for feature matching across datasets.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03592",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "matlab-package-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Feature matching across two LC-MS datasets using retention time and m/z values",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:50:22.353016+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/matlab-package-execution/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We believe the method and associated software will aid the integration of untargeted LC\u2013MS metabolomics data in a wide variety of applications such as batch combination, discovery validation, and multicohort integration.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly states the method is for untargeted LC-MS metabolomics.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03592",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "matlab-package-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Untargeted metabolomic feature matching",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:50:22.353016+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/matlab-package-execution/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The method requires only two independent feature sets (RT, MZ, FI) as inputs and follows a three-step process.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly specifies that RT and MZ are required inputs.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03592",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "matlab-package-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Input data: LC-MS untargeted metabolomic feature table with retention time and m/z columns",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:50:22.353016+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/matlab-package-execution/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "One challenge is to combine or compare datasets generated from different analytical methods, instruments, software, as well as from different batches, populations, and sample types. These factors impact a variety of variables including retention times, m/z ratios, ionization efficiency, adduct formation, detector sensitivity, number of peaks detected, etc., complicating matching of spectral features from one run to another.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes the problem M2S solves as matching datasets that have not been previously aligned, supporting the 'when NOT to use' guidance.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03592",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "matlab-package-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Input data is already aligned or pre-matched",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:50:22.353016+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/matlab-package-execution/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "As it only requires the features' retention time, m/z, and (optionally) feature intensity values (RT, MZ, FI) averaged across samples, it is simple to use and potentially applicable in the widest range of situations.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly states RT and MZ are required, supporting this constraint.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03592",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "matlab-package-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Feature tables do not contain retention time and m/z values",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:50:22.353016+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/matlab-package-execution/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "This is especially challenging in the setting of untargeted metabolomic profiling where there are thousands of spectral features, even within a single run, whose chemical identity is not known.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly focuses on untargeted metabolomics, implying it is not designed for targeted approaches.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03592",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "matlab-package-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Targeted metabolomic feature matching",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:50:22.353016+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-feature-matching-across-datasets/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The method, as applied with this package, does not have high computer memory requirements and the execution is rapid, taking less than a minute using default settings on a regular desktop computer to match datasets with around 6000 features. The toolbox is flexible to accommodate disparate dataset matching, with detailed visualizations that help guide the analyst through the process and lend confidence to the final matching results. We believe the method and associated software will aid the integration of untargeted LC\u2013MS metabolomics data in a wide variety of applications such as batch combination, discovery validation, and multicohort integration.",
      "asbval:note": "Core research question is directly supported by the paper's abstract and methods description.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-1c03592",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolite-feature-matching-across-datasets",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Match untargeted metabolomic features across two LC-MS datasets by comparing retention time and mass-to-charge ratio signatures using the M2S Matlab package.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
